<LegalLayout
  title="Price Benchmarks"
  description="How PatientBillGuide defines fair price ranges using Medicare allowed amounts."
  crumbs={[
    { label: 'Methodology', href: '/methodology/' },
    { label: 'Price Benchmarks' },
  ]}
>
  <h2>Medicare allowed amount</h2>
  <p>
    For a given CPT code and locality, we look up the CMS Medicare allowed amount — the
    payment Medicare approves before patient cost-sharing. This is a <strong>public anchor</strong>,
    not what every hospital charges.
  </p>

  <h2>Fair range heuristic</h2>
  <p>
    Commercial and self-pay prices vary widely. We display an educational range of approximately
    <strong>1.5× to 2.5×</strong> the Medicare allowed amount as a rough “typical commercial
    zone” reference, documented here for transparency.
  </p>

  <h2>How to interpret results</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Within range</strong> — may be unremarkable; still verify with your provider</li>
    <li><strong>Above range</strong> — worth asking questions; not proof of overcharging</li>
    <li><strong>Far above range</strong> — stronger signal to review line items and documentation</li>
  </ul>

  <p>
    Local market, facility fees, emergency settings, and insurance contracts all affect real
    prices. Our benchmarks are starting points for informed questions.
  </p>
</LegalLayout>
